page.title: 03TARRINGTON HOUSING
page.content: There are 2 Council Housing estates in Tarrington. The oldest estate{Garbrook}built in 1949,with 12 houses and 8 bungalows. The newer estate{Barrs Orchard completed in 1984,with 21 houses and 22 bungalows. Many of the children at this school come from the{Barrs Orchard}estate. There are no children from{Garbrook}in this school. The private houses range from farm cottages to substantial dwellings. Some of the houses have thatched roofs while others are black and white timbered.Their age range is from present day to 400 years. Most are owner occupied.Several of the dwellings are unoccupied.
